txt.en: 'Did you feel that gust? Whence did such a harsh chill arise?'
'Wait... stand back!'
'He's up at the top of what's left, ah-ha! You better not make him wait!'
Instance: The Darkness Over Lebennin
'Still your tongue, Man.'
'I did not come to feed your arrogance. I come bearing a warning.'
'You seek to deceive, but you cannot, Balakh√¥r.'
'I sense your fear at my arrival, for our Master has grown impatient with you.'
'Your worthless pillaging and displays of force are nothing to him.'
'Sail upon the river and make for the Guarded City as you were bid.'
'Do not deny your Master or far more than Umbar will be swept from this world!'
'What a worthless lot...'
'Ah, maybe this one has something valuable!'
'Dax! What took you so long?'
'I think we crushed everything worthwhile...'
'I bet this looked great once! Wouldn't you say so? Hah!'
'Ah, still no armour... you are a bold one. I cannot deny you that.'
'Look upon this land, Daxamat!'
'Well now... to what do I owe such a rarely-granted audience?'
'So much to be claimed and so few to defend it. Indeed, our victory shall be swift.'
'And what might that be?'
'The daughter of Imrahil is wise, but wisdom cannot supplant strength.'
'When we reach Pelargir, I shall see their fleet burned and their harbour broken.'
'The great wounds dealt to Umbar at the hands of their long-vanished hero shall be repaid in full.'
'And then, I shall be the master of Gondor!'
